<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4635781>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Australophialus turbonis from Turbo sarmaticus collected in False Bay. Light microscopy of external features and cirri, female. A—Lateral view of whole specimen; B—Opercular area, lateral view showing opercular bars with notch, labrum and lateral bars; C—Terminal cirri; D—Dorsal body process; E—Mouthparts, including the mandible, maxillule and maxilla; F—Labrum.Abbreviations: dp—dorsal body process, la—labrum, lb—lateral bar, md—mandible, mx1—maxillule, mx2—maxilla, rb—reinforcing bar." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4635781/files/figure.png" .

